I understand your humor, and your need for it; just thought it a bit inappropriate (but also very &quot;American&quot;) in this particular spot.  <br><br>
As I said above, I don't know the answer, but a very cursery reading of the subject suggests that the CIA didn't need to be in on either the overthrow or the assination attempt, that our government had already pulled the plug on Diem's funding, and all we had to do was to wait and watch.  <br><br>
One thing to remember, for those just joining in, was the this was 1963, and we only had about 16,500 troops in Vietnam at the time.
